The course gives a systematic overview of the Estonian history from 1550 until 1710. The course focuses on the connections of the Estonian history with that of neighbouring countries and Europe. It will touch upon such issues as the term of early modern age, historiography, Russian-Livonian war (1558-1561) and the wars between other countries over Old-Livonia until 1629/1635, ruling countries and the policy of different foreign rulers here, thereby special attention is paid to the administrative, enfeoffment and colonization policy, court system, economic development, cultural changes, etc. under Swedish rulers.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The student acquieres an overview about  the main fields of Estonian history in 1550-1710.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student acquires systematic and comprehensive knowledge about the Estonian history in 1550-1710 in the context of the histories of neighbouring and other European countries.
